It is easy to check that for any value of \(c\), the function
\( y = x^2 + \frac{c}{x^2}\)  is solution of equation
 \( xy' + 2y = 4x^2,\ (x \gt 0) \). Find the value of \( c \) for which the solution satisfies the initial condition \( y($a)= $b \).
$BR$BR

 \( c = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}
END_TEXT

$answer = "($b - $a^2)*($a^2)";

ANS(num_cmp($answer));
